                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="442743" author="yujian" created="Fri, 31 Jan 2025 01:27:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It turns out the correct version is java-11-openjdk-devel. Please refer to DCO-10120.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="442714" author="yujian" created="Thu, 30 Jan 2025 19:47:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In RHEL 9.5 kernel.spec:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;%if %{with_perf}&lt;br/&gt;
BuildRequires: zlib-devel binutils-devel newt-devel perl(ExtUtils::Embed) bison flex xz-devel&lt;br/&gt;
BuildRequires: audit-libs-devel python3-setuptools&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;&gt;BuildRequires: java-devel&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
......&lt;br/&gt;
%endif&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The java-devel package is required by building perf (Performance monitoring for the Linux kernel) for the kernel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure which &lt;font color=&quot;#172b4d&quot;&gt;version of &lt;font color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;java-devel&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt; is the correct one to meet the requirement. Can we try to find the correct one instead of changing kernel.spec? Or just disabling building the perf package?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
